	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">drk421 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Check it out:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tjcvR5McmSg">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tjcvR5McmSg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I'd love to see something like this for an NES emulator.</div>
<br />
<br />I have implemented it in NESICIDE.  The image below shows CPU RAM.  The dialog updates at VBLANK frequency, and is zoomable.  Memory accesses are logged real-time.  
<br />
<br />Clicking on the image [or selecting an address in the data view] will tell you stuff about the address you clicked on like what type of access was last, etc.  Obviously still WIP since there are dialog elements that need a bit of help.  I like the 2D C64 version though...mine reminds me more of something like Disk Defragmenter.  Ahh well, it was a nice excuse to brush up some custom controls.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.nesicide.com/images/codedatalogger.JPG" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />PPU RAM, and all ROM banks are also selectable.  
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.nesicide.com/images/codedatalogger2.JPG" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
